oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grand Ole Opry - Prince Albert - 1955-07-30 - Part 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Part 2 of Prince Albert tobacco sponsored Grand Ole Opry segment from July 30, 1955. Featuring Grant Turner (announcer), Carl Smith (host/performer), guest performers the Wilburn Brothers, and regular performers the Jordanaires, Dale Potter, Lew Childre, Del Wood, the Duke Of Paducah, and Chet Atkins. Held at Ryman Auditorium, Nashville, TN.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Duke Of Paducah; Wilburn Brothers; Chet Atkins; Carl Smith
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Comedy routine (Duke Of Paducah) -- I'm A Ding Dong Daddy (From Dumas) (Duke Of Paducah) -- Carl Smith introduces the Wilburn Brothers -- Let Me Be The First To Know (Wilburn Brothers) -- Carl Smith introduces Chet Atkins -- Red Wing (Chet Atkins) -- Carl Smith talks -- I Just Dropped In To Say Goodbye (Carl Smith) -- Closing theme -- Closing statement (Carl Smith) -- Cavalier Cigarettes commercial -- Station announcements
